}}
The tree stands approximately 30 meters tall, with a trunk circumference of 24.2 meters measured at a height of 1.3 meters above ground level, and a root spread of 33.5 meters. An internal cavity measuring about 13 square meters (equivalent to eight tatami mats) has been detected within the trunk. Its age is estimated at around 1500 years (as of [[:en:Heisei era|Heisei]] 23 ([[:en:2011|2011]])). A survey conducted by the {{ill|Environmental Agency|ja|環境庁|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Environmental Agency|qq=|ja_comment=jawiki redirects to 環境省|ja_comment=jawiki redirects to 環境省}} in Showa 63 ([[:en:1988|1988]]) recognized it as the largest giant tree in Japan. It is also sometimes referred to as "Kamō no Ōkus" (蒲生の大楠) or "Kamō no Ōkus" (蒲生の大クス).

